## Verification

1. `npx vite build` - compiles without errors
2. Draw a single wall (click-move-click) - wall appears, preview disappears
3. Shift-draw - wall constrains to 0/45/90 degree increments
4. Draw near existing endpoint - snaps to it
5. Shift-draw near endpoint - constraint overrides snap (wall goes to constrained angle, not snap point)
6. Preview line matches final wall position in all above cases
7. Chain: after placing wall A, draw wall B from A's endpoint - snap to A works (tests stale closure fix)
8. Double-click / Escape terminates chain
9. Length label shows during preview above the line
